c cosine (inverse cosine) of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`acosh`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.acosh","kind":"opaque","line":394,"name":"Float.acosh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L394-L400"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.asinh\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">asinh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic arc sine (inverse sine) of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`asinh`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.asinh","kind":"opaque","line":387,"name":"Float.asinh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L387-L393"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.tanh\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">tanh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic tangent of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`tanh`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.tanh","kind":"opaque","line":380,"name":"Float.tanh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L380-L386"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.cosh\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">cosh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic cosine of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`cosh`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.cosh","kind":"opaque","line":373,"name":"Float.cosh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L373-L379"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.sinh\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">sinh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic sine of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`sinh`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.sinh","kind":"opaque","line":366,"name":"Float.sinh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L366-L372"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.atan2\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">atan2</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">y </span><span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the arc tangent (inverse tangent) of `y / x` in radians, in the range `-π`–`π`. The signs\nof the arguments determine the quadrant of the result.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`atan2`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.atan2","kind":"opaque","line":358,"name":"Float.atan2","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L358-L365"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.atan\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">atan</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the arc tangent (inverse tangent) of a floating-point number in radians.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`atan`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.atan","kind":"opaque","line":351,"name":"Float.atan","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L351-L357"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.acos\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">acos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the arc cosine (inverse cosine) of a floating-point number in radians.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`acos`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.acos","kind":"opaque","line":344,"name":"Float.acos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L344-L350"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.asin\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">asin</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the arc sine (inverse sine) of a floating-point number in radians.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`asin`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float.asin","kind":"opaque","line":337,"name":"Float.asin","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float.lean#L337-L343"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\"